snippet.textDisplay: New employer hands managerial job to young inexperienced candidate. First thing young candidate foolishly asks for is mega bucks to buy new workers as the ones already there aren’t good enough. What possible message does this send to the employers? That this guy might not be up to the task, sowing doubts in their minds. Can’t wait for this window to end, so that Senor Arteta doesn’t have to field stupid repetitive transfer questions from journalists and also the day to day unrealistic expectation from us fans that some new marquee player will sign and solve all our woes. Arteta; first and foremost, is intelligently fixing the mentality of the players and the energy around the club so that if a new signing comes in, the club is already on it’s way in a new system so new signee can flourish. Let’s give him the time needed to turn this around and kudos to all the fans not getting on Mustafi’s back this week. We all know his limitations but supporting our team right now is super crucial above being super critical. We can turn the emirates into a fortress of noise and energy that unsettles opponents. No doubt the players felt the energy of our away supporters at Stamford Bridge and used that energy to galvanise themselves.

snippet.textDisplay: Funny enough Robbie, Martinelli's goal was only possible due to Mustafi winning an aerial battle and putting the ball out into space,  a space that Mustafi told him to hold before the corner was taken. So it begs the question of what do we really need at the back? Are we replacing Luiz, Chambers or Holding with this new signing? I do think we need an element of steel around the back which Papa or Mustafi provide, but they both have some mind-numbing moments  more often than not. To me the new guy seems like a more competent/competitive version of Chambers. All our young CBs have show glimpses of the qualities needed they just need games to get the consistency (Chambers, Holding, Mavro) all need to be playing weekly for a full season. Hopefully Saliba is a revelation and Pablo.

snippet.textDisplay: We really need an attacker too though. We talk about this trio of Auba-Laca-Pepe but we're struggling to score goals here. I just don't think something is right in this attack and I can't put my finger on it. It's just not working and it's been like this for a while too. I'd also like Martinelli to play either through the middle or behind the striker. He's too good to be out wide imo. I feel signing an attacker would lift the team altogether and hopefully bring more urgency and purpose to the attacks because that is something we're lacking atm.
